Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.19,0:01:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}No matter who they are,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.52,0:01:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}all people carry many sorts of memories\N{\c&He1e1e1&}within their hearts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Painful memories, which they\N{\c&He1e1e1&}wish they could get rid of...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Precious memories, which they wish they\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could keep in their hearts forever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}They could just be what a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}person's life amounts to,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}as well as a testament to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that person being alive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.95,0:02:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Corridors of Memories"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.26,0:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Two whole days off, huh?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Even electromagnetic interference
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}at Ariadre Junction can be a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}nice thing once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I guess so. But once it's over,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we have to leave immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.27,0:02:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's fine. It's been a long time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}since I've had a good meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Never mind food, let's toss some back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.27,0:02:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This feels great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This sure is a pretty place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.61,0:02:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Graz Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.28,0:02:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Planet Dio here is famous for the ruins\N{\c&He1e1e1&}left by its indigenous peoples.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.95,0:02:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It won't hurt to take it easy here in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a place with so much greenery, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.62,0:02:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.95,0:02:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And here I thought you were a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}fiend for work, Captain Bulge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.29,0:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, I guess I'm no match\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for natural phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.56,0:03:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rest well, because once\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you've built up your spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll make sure to have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you back working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.23,0:03:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not just all\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the natural beauty here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.70,0:03:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}there's also a certain unusual air\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about this planet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes, there is. These people\N{\c&He1e1e1&}watch over their ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.51,0:03:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and maybe because of that, there are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}lots of mythical stories about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.24,0:03:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I think I'm going to like that about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.58,0:03:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not as though {\i1}you'll{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}get to meet him, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.60,0:03:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh? Where are David and Bruce?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.26,0:03:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.27,0:03:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Over here, over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're already at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.61,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Empty, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.27,0:03:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, share some of yours with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.94,0:03:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:03:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh? What's that you're drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.61,0:03:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, you can at least get a little\N{\c&He1e1e1&}rowdy at a time like this, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.95,0:04:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Especially with how\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reckless you always are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Cut that out, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, no matter how\N{\c&He1e1e1&}many lives I've got,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}it's not enough to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}working alongside you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.23,0:04:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look at it from where we're standing,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}would you? Right, Bruce?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't take him for even one minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't always have to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}keep saying that, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm trying my hardest here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your hardest, your hardest...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.47,0:04:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It must be nice to be able to say that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and have everything slide, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's not a child. Now go drink quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Geez, Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, pup, you've got spunk, huh?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you guys here to see Salye, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're so young, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't have any memories you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}want to get rid of yet, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But that dour-looking fellow over there\N{\c&He1e1e1&}looks like he's got a bundle!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um... who's Salye?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.94,0:04:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you're here, Salye will come and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}steal away any memories you don't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Steal away your memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.28,0:05:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But then, he's probably just the product\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of someone's wishful imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.22,0:05:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone has a memory or two that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}they'd like to get rid of, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, there you are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}there you are, Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You went off and disappeared\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all by yourself, so I got worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, I had something on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.90,0:05:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you still upset\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about what Bruce said?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not really. That's not what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Eating something sweet\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will cheer you up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.58,0:05:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a chocolate\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that I keep set aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but I think under the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}circumstances I can give it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Psych!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.26,0:05:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, do you have any memories\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you wouldn't want to lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've got a whole host of them,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}more than I can count.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A whole host?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:05:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Like the dictation test\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that I tore up and threw away,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or that dress that I ruined\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by spilling ice cream on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Or that time I got into a fight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with Papa and broke his favorite...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.21,0:06:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No problem. I thought it would\N{\c&He1e1e1&}be something more serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you mean!?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}They're all important memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't have a single memory that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I would want to do away with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're all precious treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how painful\N{\c&He1e1e1&}those memories may be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is this what's so important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So this is the embodiment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of your memories, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Give that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not my thing, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.24,0:06:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who was that guy!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.25,0:06:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He couldn't have been the one\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from that story earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Memories I'd like to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}do away with, huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.21,0:07:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you Bruce?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is too cold.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, this is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Headquarters is a big place.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I've been looking all over for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.55,0:07:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm Owen, your new partner\N{\c&He1e1e1&}starting today. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.56,0:07:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't partner with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's a rookie, so he doesn't know better.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be so hard on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hot-t-t-t!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry up and take this, partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.24,0:07:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I told you, I don't need a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Bruce the Grim Reaper," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've lost two others already.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.92,0:07:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hmph! So you already know, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.25,0:07:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've got a lot of nerve waltzing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in here like this when you know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.92,0:08:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you want to run, now's your chance.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Or is it that you'd rather die, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.53,0:08:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Cut it out, Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.86,0:08:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're the one who's going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.20,0:08:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am Owen the Immortal, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.87,0:08:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I will be your third partner, and your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}last partner! You should be grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.54,0:08:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's cold! This is your fault\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for making us wait too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.21,0:08:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Anyhow, I'm going to bust you down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}from "Bruce the Grim Reaper" to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just plain "Bruce." Brace yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.56,0:08:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, that was nothing to laugh over!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Sheesh, how disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey now, are those Bruce the Grim\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Reaper's Blues? This is too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.25,0:09:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well then, what would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.85,0:09:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Starting now, we're going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have some Immortal Rock n' Roll!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, way to go, Owen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.58,0:09:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What was I doing just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who is this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, well. Looks like\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I got a little drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.00,0:10:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You'd better get to bed soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He... couldn't have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You really don't remember\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what happened yesterday!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And not just yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.29,0:10:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is all this,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so early in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Three years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.62,0:10:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not what I mean!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm talking about Owen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.63,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yo, Yuuki! You haven't eaten yet,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}right? Come eat with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:10:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was Salye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then that boy really was him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.57,0:11:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you guys have something stolen, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.91,0:11:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce had his memories taken.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Some important memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.92,0:11:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that true? You had your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}memories stolen from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.96,0:11:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You really can't remember them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.93,0:11:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you babbling on about?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you saying something is wrong with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.93,0:11:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Remember, Bruce! Do you really intend\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to forget about him like this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aren't they important to you?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Speaking just for myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.60,0:11:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}there isn't anything that I'd want\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to lose, no matter what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.61,0:11:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, if you forget,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}then who will remember Owen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shut up, would you?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I haven't lost a single memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.28,0:11:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}What's wrong? How come I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}feel so uncomfortable?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:11:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I felt fine up until a little while ago...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Monsieur!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.63,0:12:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You must have gone through\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something painful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.23,0:12:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How did Salye take your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}memories from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mademoiselle, is this some\N{\c&He1e1e1&}new form of pick-up line?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.57,0:12:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right, you don't remember.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.91,0:12:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why? Why won't he come to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mademoi--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't like being chased after.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.59,0:12:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Salye! Is that you, Salye!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Salye?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Salye, please! Steal my memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It hurts too much to remember him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.60,0:12:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, are you all right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mademoiselle...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.27,0:12:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good day. It's such pleasant weather,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, what have you done!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.62,0:12:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you steal her memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.23,0:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it possible that he\N{\c&He1e1e1&}took my memories, too...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.23,0:13:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, the story is true, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, did you know about Salye?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.90,0:13:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, but I thought it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}was the kind of legend
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that every planet has one or two of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.91,0:13:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, where's Bruce?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's not in the hotel.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}David is hunting him down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.91,0:13:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I thought that maybe Yuki\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could do something for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.92,0:13:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is Bruce-{\i1}san{\i0} ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay, Yuki.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce isn't exactly sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see. We've received a message from the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}observation office at Ariadne Junction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...that the electromagnetic interference\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will subside in about nine hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Understood. Head on back now and stand by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.60,0:13:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.27,0:13:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, is it really true that Bruce\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has had his memories stolen from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.61,0:13:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's how it appears.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll leave in nine hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.28,0:13:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tell Bruce and David for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.95,0:14:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to be leaving like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There isn't anything we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's up to Bruce whether he\N{\c&He1e1e1&}gets his memories back or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.22,0:14:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.56,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's go, Louis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.56,0:14:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There might be something\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that we can do. Besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.23,0:14:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that's not the real Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.57,0:14:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mm-hmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just what is it that was stolen from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What have I forgotten...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's go find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.22,0:15:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You think we can really get it back\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by searching blindly like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.89,0:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to get it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He seemed like a smart-alecky,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}stubborn little brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh yeah, Bruce,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that able from yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, what would you do if you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}really were to run into this Salye?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.24,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What memories would I want to lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about you? What would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've had your heart broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.01,0:15:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as having a dramatic,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}penniless past yourself, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.91,0:15:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean Irene? Don't even go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wouldn't mind giving that one away,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.38,0:15:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but I don't feel comfortable\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with having it stolen from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, should we bet on it? One able\N{\c&He1e1e1&}says you'll have your memories stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If they get stolen, then I'll\N{\c&He1e1e1&}forget about it anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you get yours stolen,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll take this from you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A bet is a bet, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.27,0:15:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Lucky for you, it was my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't intend to forget about Irene.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It may hurt, but I was still young.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.21,0:16:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder what I really meant to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.88,0:16:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}At first, it was like a great weight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}had been lifted from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.92,0:16:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and I felt delighted. But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I feel empty... like a hole\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has been opened up inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.58,0:16:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, kid! Come on out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.58,0:16:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We need to talk to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.58,0:16:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What have you come here for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.58,0:16:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't need anything\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in particular from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is about the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}memories you took from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.59,0:16:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you mean this memory,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not giving it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm especially fond of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.93,0:16:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're not asking you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do it for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.53,0:17:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How about we make a bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.30,0:17:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If this coin comes up heads,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'll return Bruce's memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If it's tails, the coin and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the memories are yours to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.54,0:17:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Haven't you ever seen a coin? Here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who is that pretty woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.88,0:17:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's Queen Millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, what will it be? This coin is packed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with memories from both me and Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That not a bad deal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll do it, I'll do it! I want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm uncovering it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.90,0:17:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That means we win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You promised. Let's have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce's memory back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.57,0:17:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you know what happens to folks\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that don't keep their promises?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.91,0:17:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}This{\i0} is what happens to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll give it back to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.25,0:17:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David! Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:18:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Salye... You found your memories, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.53,0:18:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, how does he get his memories back?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You just have to throw it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}against that rock there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.53,0:18:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.87,0:18:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's wrong? Don't you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}want your memories back?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.87,0:18:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.87,0:18:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can't! After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...it's because it hurts that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}it's important to you, right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.56,0:18:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Take care of his weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.89,0:18:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Give us trouble, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.23,0:18:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That settles that. Shall we get going?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.57,0:18:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.24,0:18:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen! Stay with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.24,0:18:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, call Yuki! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.91,0:18:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn... I blew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.58,0:18:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.92,0:19:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't worry... this isn't your fault...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm the one who was careless...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.86,0:19:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't talk! Yuki will be here right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.19,0:19:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.19,0:19:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I told you... I'm immortal, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.87,0:19:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.87,0:19:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just watch... I'll prove you're not...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Grim Reaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.54,0:19:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen... Owen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This isn't happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.21,0:19:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Owen!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.89,0:19:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're a strange fellow. And here I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}stole it from you and everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.90,0:19:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You probably wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.23,0:19:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are those who won't feel at ease,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}even once their scars disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.90,0:19:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I thought I was making everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let me show you a way you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}can do this without stealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.58,0:20:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Use that to gamble with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.65,0:20:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you win, you can have them\N{\c&He1e1e1&}tell you their memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.25,0:20:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What if I lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.58,0:20:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then you can tell them one of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.92,0:20:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Goodbye, Salye. I may come\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to see you again someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.93,0:20:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.60,0:20:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}There are times when memories\N{\c&He1e1e1&}can become too heavy to bear.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.27,0:20:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}However, it isn't until a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}person loses their memories{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.18,0:20:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}that they first realize how important\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the pain of carrying them really is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.28,0:20:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.62,0:20:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop loafing around!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Our vacation is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.62,0:20:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maybe we were better off with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the cheerful, kind Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.29,0:20:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Uh-uh. It wasn't like him,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and it made me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.63,0:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.97,0:20:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you have something taken from you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.30,0:21:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The chocolate I put in here is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I sure do like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.27,0:21:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.29,0:22:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Constantly having dreams of the hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.97,0:22:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The smiles and tears that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}come to mind every time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and I set forth again toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.99,0:22:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The joyful light of the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.60,0:22:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.60,0:22:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how far apart we are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.28,0:23:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}My heart wishes always\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be at your side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.97,0:23:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I'm just a sexaroid.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.30,0:23:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Why would you try to defend me,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when I'm not even a person?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.97,0:23:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Next time on Tales of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways, Episode 10:{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.58,0:23:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Turning Point"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.98,0:23:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to encounter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something at the next station.{\i0}